<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1863-06-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1863-06-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="212" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d212">
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Adams</persName>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 622.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi></placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1863-06-10"><hi rend="italic">June</hi> 10, 1863.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> Your despatch of May 21, No. 417, has been
                            received. The very spirited and just resolutions of the citizens of
                            York, which accompany it, have been submitted to the President, and
                            received by him with the highest satisfaction. My previous instructions
                            will, I trust, be a sufficient guide for you in making a proper
                            acknowledgment of the resolutions on his behalf.</p>
                        <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Charles Francis Adams</hi>, Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi></p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>